# Security / Secrets / Safety

- Never commit API keys or secrets.
- Use .env.local for local dev; provide .env.example without real values.
- Log hygiene:
  - Do not log full prompts + user inputs by default (can contain sensitive data).
  - Never log API keys, secrets, or tokens (no console.log(key) or similar).
  - If needed, add explicit "debug mode" guard.
- Key exposure: API responses must never include raw API keys or encryptedKey; only return booleans (e.g. "configured") or opaque identifiers.

Prompt safety:
- Treat prompts/results as untrusted strings.
- Escape outputs properly in UI to prevent injection issues.
- If we store images/results, validate content types and size limits.
